fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data.types

Interface IBinaryData

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IData<IBinaryType>

    public interface IBinaryData
extends IData<IBinaryType>
    Provides typed access to binary data for a cell, such as files.

    The data value is of type byte[]. The value may be set using byte[] or by using the writer.

    Thread-safety: implementations of this interface are not required to be safe for concurrent access. Therefore, processing should generally not be shared between multiple threads.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

      • getFileName

        String getFileName()
        Gets the file name associated with this binary data, if known. The file name may be directly accessible via this data object, or via a delegate cell defined by IBinaryType.getFileNameCell(). In other cases, the file name may be undefined (this ultimately depends upon the storage model).
        Returns:
        the filename, or null.
        Since:

      • setFileName

        void setFileName(String fileName)
          throws UnsupportedOperationException
        Sets the file name associated with this binary data, when the underlying storage model supports this data attribute. If a delegate cell is defined by IBinaryType.getFileNameCell(), then setting this value immediately sets the value of the delegate cell.
        Parameters:
        fileName - the file name. An empty value (or null implies that a default value may be assigned when storing the item containing this data cell.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - if the underlying storage model does not support this data attribute and when there is no defined delegate cell.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getFileType

        String getFileType()
        Gets the file media type associated with this binary data, if known. The media type may be directly accessible via this data object, or via a delegate cell defined by IBinaryType.getFileTypeCell(). In other cases, the media type may be undefined (this ultimately depends upon the storage model).
        Returns:

      • setFileType

        void setFileType(String fileType)
          throws UnsupportedOperationException
        Sets the file media type associated with this binary data, when the underlying storage model supports this data attribute. If a delegate cell is defined by IBinaryType.getFileTypeCell(), then setting this value immediately sets the value of the delegate cell.
        Parameters:
        fileType - the file media type, in standard MIME format. An empty value (or null implies that a default value may be assigned when storing the item containing this data cell.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - if the underlying storage model does not support this data attribute and when there is no defined delegate cell.
        Since:
        1.0
